slides.title: Actors in the controversy
slides.text: Network visualization, created using Gephi. The nodes size shows degree (in/out>3) and colours reveal macro-actors belonging.

slides.title: Academic cluster
slides.text: Bigger and more connected clusterin the network. Many nodes are academic institutions and publishers' houses websites. This can give some information regarding the contribution of academic institutions and specific projects to the controversy (e.g. digital sociology or the social data lab). However, a deeper investigation of the controversy in academia will be developed in the second analytical chapter.

slides.title: NGOs/Association cluster
slides.text: NGOs and Associations are the second largest cluster/community in the network. Overall less connected than the academic one, they are divided in smaller communities on the basis of their area of interest/intervention. Particularly well connected appears NGOs and Associations working on children protection online.

slides.title: Private companies cluster
slides.text: Private companies are among the most populated categories. However, they do not connect much within the cluster. This could be due to the high variety in the internal composition of the category.

slides.title: Newsmedia cluster
slides.text: Newsmedia were willingly eliminated from the list of URLs composing the network. However, some of them reappeared as crawled entities. This confirms the fact that overall newsmedia is the most widespread and better connected category of actor in the controversy.

slides.title: Government and governmental bodies cluster
slides.text: Even though very scarcely populated these clusters occupy the central position and the central nodes in the network. The UK government website appears to be particularly relevant in the animation of the controversy online.

slides.title: Bloggers cluster
slides.text: The network shows the presence of bloggers discussing the issue. However, they are quite isolated the ones from the others. Bloggers connect more with other clusters, such as academia or NGOs.

slides.title: Actors according to Keyword
slides.text: There is a balanced presence of actors connected to freedom of speech/hate speech keywords
